  "enhanced_information": "In herpes simplex encephalitis, the first-line treatment is Acyclovir, which is well-established as effective against the herpes simplex virus. Vidarabine is an alternative treatment but is less commonly used due to its side effects and lower efficacy compared to Acyclovir. Ganciclovir is primarily indicated for cytomegalovirus infections and is not effective for herpes simplex virus, thus it is not used in this context. Amantadine is an antiviral primarily used for influenza and does not have a role in treating herpes simplex encephalitis. Therefore, the correct answer to the question is Amantadine, as it is not indicated for herpes simplex encephalitis."
